President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Kenneth R. Weinstein as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Japan. Weinstein is currently the President and CEO of Hudson Institute in Washington, D.C. He has held various positions at Hudson Institute since 1999 and is also the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the U.S. Agency for Global Media. Weinstein serves on the Advisory Committee on Trade Policy and Negotiations and is a member of the International Advisory Board of the Aspen Institute Prague, the Board of Directors of ELNET-France, and the Advisory Board of the Forum for Jewish Leadership. He has previously held positions at the Shalem Center, the Heritage Foundation, and the New Citizenship Project. Weinstein holds a B.A. from the University of Chicago, an M.Phil. from Sciences Po (Paris), and a Ph.D. from Harvard University. He is fluent in French and German.